Hindi Livinus, Yola The Adamawa State Police Command says it has arrested 30 persons in connection with clashes at Tingno, where over 30 persons were feared killed. The state government on Sunday night imposed a 24 hour curfew on Lamurde Local Government Area where the communal clashes triggered by an argument over pork between some Hausa Fulani youths and their Chobo-speaking  neighbours turned violent that  claimed lives and rendered hundreds homeless. The Commissioner of Police in the state, Olugbenga Adesanya, on Monday, in a statement signed by DSP Suleiman Nguroje, said the suspects were arrested with dane guns, swords, and cutlasses. The statement read, “The Command sees the 24 hour curfew imposed on Lamurde Local Government by the state government as a measure to contain the escalation of the crises across the local government area. “The command, in collaboration with sister security agencies, will commence the full enforcement of the directives effective from today, Monday, 18th May, 2020.” The commissioner appealed to members of the general public to respectfully comply with the orders, warning that security had been deployed to support the area commander and DPO to enforce the government directives. Copyright PUNCH.
